{"vegetarian": false, "glutenFree": false, "title": "Almond Sandies", "veryPopular": false, "gaps": "no", "sourceUrl": "http://www.foodista.com/recipe/5PSVTNDL/almond-sandies", "sourceName": "Foodista", "vegan": false, "sustainable": false, "instructions": "<ol><li>In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add extract; mix well. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Fold in almonds. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 300 degrees for 22-24 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1-2 minutes before removing to a wire rack.</li><li>Yield: about 4dozen.</li><li>NOTES : \"'Buttery, rich and delicious, Almond Sandies are my husband's favorite cookie and very popular where ever I take them,' remarks Joyce Pierce of Caldonia, Michigan.\"</li></ol>", "aggregateLikes": 1, "dairyFree": true, "extendedIngredients": [{"aisle": "Baking", "unitLong": "teaspoon", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1 teaspoon Almond extract", "name": "almond extract"}, {"aisle": "Baking", "unitLong": "teaspoons", "amount": 0.25, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1/4 teaspoon Baking powder", "name": "baking powder"}, {"aisle": "Baking", "unitLong": "teaspoons", "amount": 0.5, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "originalString": "1/2 teaspoon Baking soda", "name": "baking soda"}, {"aisle": "Milk, Eggs, Other Dairy", "unitLong": "cup", "amount": 1.0, "unitShort": "c", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "cup", "originalString": "1 cup Butter or margarine, softened", "name": "butter"}, {"aisle": "Baking", "unitLong": "cups", "amount": 1.75, "unitShort": "c", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "cups", "originalString": "1 3/4 cups All-purpose flour", "name": "flour"}, {"aisle": "Spices and Seasonings", "unitLong": "teaspoons", "amount": 0.25, "unitShort": "t", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "teaspoon", "or